codex
Implemented the GTK4 patch logic in [scripts/patch-swiftopenui-gtk-css.sh](/Users/jperla/claude/QuillUI/.swarm/worktrees/codex-issue-3/scripts/patch-swiftopenui-gtk-css.sh) and added coverage in [QuillDataSourceLoweringTests.swift](/Users/jperla/claude/QuillUI/.swarm/worktrees/codex-issue-3/Tests/QuillDataTests/QuillDataSourceLoweringTests.swift).

What changed:
- Finite flexible frames like `.frame(maxWidth: 680)` now pass `expandsToFillWidth` into `computeFrameLayout`, so GTK resolves the frame to the capped width instead of intrinsic text width.
- The same is applied symmetrically for finite `maxHeight`.
- Existing `.frame(maxWidth: .infinity)` behavior remains handled by the parent-flexible path.
- Test fixture now asserts the SwiftOpenUI patcher preserves this frame sizing fix.

Verified:
- `bash -n scripts/patch-swiftopenui-gtk-css.sh`
- `git diff --check`
- Applied the patcher to a `/tmp` copy of the real SwiftOpenUI checkout and reran it to confirm idempotence.

